  15. ‌let overhead block slot obj =
  16.   1. -. float_of_int((block / slot) * obj) /. float_of_int block

  18. ‌let max_overhead = 0.10

  20. ‌let rec blocksizes block slot = function
  21.   | 0 -> []
  22.   | obj ->
  23.     if overhead block slot obj > max_overhead
  24.     then
  25.       if overhead block obj obj < max_overhead then
  26.         obj :: blocksizes block obj (obj - 1)
  27.       else
  28.         failwith (Format.sprintf
  29.           "%d-word objects cannot fit in %d-word arena below %.1f%% overhead"
  30.                                  obj block (100. *. max_overhead))
  31.     else blocksizes block slot (obj - 1)

  33. ‌let rec findi_acc i p = function
  34.   | [] -> raise Not_found
  35.   | x :: xs -> if p x then i else findi_acc (i + 1) p xs
  36. ‌let findi = findi_acc 0

  38. ‌let arena = 4096
  39. ‌let header_size = 4
  40. ‌let max_slot = 128
  41. ‌let avail_arena = arena - header_size
  42. ‌let sizes = List.rev (blocksizes avail_arena max_int max_slot)

  44. ‌let rec size_slots n =
  45.   if n > max_slot then
  46.     []
  47.   else
  48.     findi (fun x -> n <= x) sizes :: size_slots (n + 1)

  50. let rec wastage =
  51.   sizes |> List.map (fun s -> avail_arena mod s)

  53. open Format

  55. let rec print_overheads n = function
  56.   | [] -> ()
  57.   | s :: ss when n > s -> print_overheads n ss
  58.   | (s :: _) as ss  ->
  59.      printf "%3d/%-3d: %.1f%%\n" n s (100. *. overhead avail_arena s n);
  60.      print_overheads (n+1) ss

  62. (* let () = print_overheads 1 sizes *)

  64. ‌let rec print_list ppf = function
  65.   | [] -> ()
  66.   | [x] -> fprintf ppf "%d" x
  67.   | x :: xs -> fprintf ppf "%d,@ %a" x print_list xs
